metadata.name: #01 ANUBIS STATUE
metadata.description:
ZUMA VALLEY EXPEDITION:

57th day at the Valley.
After 2 weeks of heavy rains, we were finally able to find one of the Busts. 
According to Monsieur Leclerc, it is expected to be found 6 more Statues on this Valley.
The positioning of the 7 statues will indicate the direction and distance of the buried Pylon.
The foreign commissioners and local authorities are also becoming enthusiastic.
The goal is to find the underground Temple. 
This first Anubis bust is already being shipped to Grenoble. 
The expedition already evolved from expected projections to something tangible.
We are dealing with a lot of muddy soil, which ironically is helping us with the excavations.
The superstitious ones are already saying that higher forces are leading us to find the Temple.
Many more excavation days will come, and a mix of uplifting moments and Valley sunsets are expected.
